07/06/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The chairman of the State Election Commission (SEC), Stevo Pendarovski, has resigned in order to return to his post as presidential adviser.
Pendarovski, who formerly advised the late President Boris Trajkovski on national security issues, will now do the same for incumbent President Branko Crvenkovski.
SEC Deputy Chairman Safet Aliu will act as interim SEC chief.
(Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax, A1 TV - 06/06/05)
